WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.675 --> 00:00:09.677
[theme music playing]

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

3
00:01:57.243 --> 00:01:59.245
[muffled yelling]

4
00:02:07.211 --> 00:02:10.381
[somber music playing]

5
00:02:10.465 --> 00:02:12.467
[indistinct shouting]

6
00:02:12.550 --> 00:02:13.550
[man] Come on!

7
00:02:14.260 --> 00:02:16.220
- [man grunts]
- [woman screaming]

8
00:02:25.521 --> 00:02:27.523
[dog barking]

9
00:02:40.661 --> 00:02:42.663
[indistinct shouting]

10
00:02:49.212 --> 00:02:52.632
I'll kill them! I'll kill them all!

11
00:02:52.715 --> 00:02:56.302
Traitors and villains!
They dare strike at me!

12
00:02:56.386 --> 00:02:58.096
- Your Grace. Your Grace.
- I am the king!

13
00:02:58.179 --> 00:02:59.514
Yes. Yes.

14
00:02:59.597 --> 00:03:01.057
- I am the king!
- Yes. Your Grace.

15
00:03:01.140 --> 00:03:03.226
- Please. Your Grace.
- [breathing heavily]

16
00:03:03.309 --> 00:03:04.936
Traitors and villains!

17
00:03:06.604 --> 00:03:07.939
[grunts] Fire from the sky.

18
00:03:08.898 --> 00:03:11.692
This is war! I declare war!

19
00:03:12.777 --> 00:03:14.821
I declare war!

20
00:03:14.904 --> 00:03:16.948
[somber music continues playing]

21
00:04:11.043 --> 00:04:12.837
[Otto] The gates have been shut.

22
00:04:14.714 --> 00:04:16.174
The search progresses.

23
00:04:17.758 --> 00:04:19.302
The villain will be found.

24
00:04:21.345 --> 00:04:23.306
We mustn't be shaken by this...

25
00:04:27.852 --> 00:04:29.061
This act.

26
00:04:33.149 --> 00:04:35.568
- The child...
- The child is dead.

27
00:04:39.155 --> 00:04:40.323
His pain is ended.

28
00:04:44.494 --> 00:04:47.121
[voice breaking]
But what they've done to my girl...

29
00:04:47.830 --> 00:04:49.540
- Yes.
- [sobbing]

30
00:04:56.797 --> 00:04:58.633
[Alicent sniffles. then sobs softly]

31
00:05:00.927 --> 00:05:02.428
[Alicent breathing heavily]

32
00:05:03.346 --> 00:05:05.431
And they will pay for this.

33
00:05:06.057 --> 00:05:08.059
[sniffles. then sobbing softly]

34
00:05:10.061 --> 00:05:11.103
[sniffles]

35
00:05:14.565 --> 00:05:17.026
[breathing heavily]

36
00:05:17.109 --> 00:05:19.445
- Who will pay?
- Whosever hand did this

37
00:05:19.529 --> 00:05:21.030
or caused it to be done.

38
00:05:21.113 --> 00:05:24.992
And what if the hand that's done it
is not who must be blamed?

39
00:05:27.036 --> 00:05:30.122
The gods punish us. They punish me.

40
00:05:30.665 --> 00:05:31.916
[sobs]

41
00:05:31.999 --> 00:05:33.334
For what sin?

42
00:05:37.630 --> 00:05:39.048
Daughter. listen to me.

43
00:05:39.131 --> 00:05:41.884
We will mourn as we must. but...

44
00:05:43.427 --> 00:05:45.972
some good may yet come of this.

45
00:05:48.683 --> 00:05:52.353
And where were the members of this council
while the murderer threatened their king?

46
00:05:52.436 --> 00:05:54.814
- Were you also threatened. Your Grace?
- I could've been!

47
00:05:54.897 --> 00:05:56.023
[pot shatters]

48
00:05:58.693 --> 00:06:01.112
My son is my legacy!

49
00:06:02.572 --> 00:06:05.241
My son is heir to the Iron Throne!

50
00:06:07.201 --> 00:06:08.202
And where were you?

51
00:06:08.869 --> 00:06:10.663
The Lord Commander of my Kingsguard.

52
00:06:10.746 --> 00:06:13.124
I was abed. Your Grace.
having ordered the night's watch.

53
00:06:14.083 --> 00:06:15.084
Abed.

54
00:06:16.002 --> 00:06:17.003
Abed!

55
00:06:18.129 --> 00:06:20.965
Instead of safeguarding
the sanctity of my family.

56
00:06:21.632 --> 00:06:24.510
This is not the time
for blind accusations. Your Grace.

57
00:06:24.594 --> 00:06:26.262
We'll know who did this soon enough.

58
00:06:26.345 --> 00:06:31.392
Who did this? Who... What?
Is there any question who did this?

59
00:06:31.475 --> 00:06:34.770
Who would do this
save the Bitch Queen of Bastards.

60
00:06:34.854 --> 00:06:37.523
the Smug Cunt of Dragonstone?

61
00:06:37.607 --> 00:06:40.985
There she sits across the bay.
on her rock. laughing at me.

62
00:06:41.068 --> 00:06:43.446
- She's fucking laughing at me!
- [glass shatters]

63
00:06:51.996 --> 00:06:53.623
You wished her life to be spared.

64
00:06:53.706 --> 00:06:58.419
If I may. Your Grace. My lords.
The guard has detained someone.

65
00:06:59.462 --> 00:07:01.464
The man we apprehended is known to us.

66
00:07:02.798 --> 00:07:06.427
He's a gold cloak.
noted for his brutal nature.

67
00:07:06.510 --> 00:07:09.055
We caught him
fleeing the Gate of the Gods.

68
00:07:09.138 --> 00:07:11.182
with the child's head in a sack.

69
00:07:13.893 --> 00:07:15.061
I'll kill him myself.

70
00:07:15.144 --> 00:07:18.272
We'd do well to get what information
we can from the blackguard.

71
00:07:20.483 --> 00:07:23.319
I trust in the mastery of your trade.
Lord Larys.

72
00:07:23.402 --> 00:07:26.989
Oh. always studying. always protocol.
We know our enemy!

73
00:07:27.073 --> 00:07:30.242
[Ironrod] A king may have
more than one enemy. Your Grace.

74
00:07:30.326 --> 00:07:33.496
We would do well to ascertain
if this is your sister's hand...

75
00:07:34.288 --> 00:07:37.583
or if there is a serpent
nestled closer to our bosoms.

76
00:07:37.667 --> 00:07:39.377
I suppose you're right. Ironrod.

77
00:07:40.753 --> 00:07:41.879
Could be anyone.

78
00:07:43.464 --> 00:07:46.175
It could be any one of you in this room.

79
00:07:56.686 --> 00:07:58.729
Lord Jasper is correct.

80
00:07:59.397 --> 00:08:02.441
In one sense.
we must determine what happened

81
00:08:02.525 --> 00:08:04.527
and if we in the Keep are still in peril.

82
00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:06.445
In another sense. of course...

83
00:08:09.407 --> 00:08:10.658
it doesn't matter.

84
00:08:14.078 --> 00:08:15.788
You mean to blame Rhaenyra.

85
00:08:16.914 --> 00:08:18.833
Tell the realm she has done this.

86
00:08:18.916 --> 00:08:22.545
[Aegon] I'll have the realm told nothing.
We were assaulted within our own walls.

87
00:08:22.628 --> 00:08:26.382
Within our own beds.
I will not be seen as weak.

88
00:08:26.465 --> 00:08:28.509
You're already seen as weak. Aegon.

89
00:08:30.010 --> 00:08:31.345
You fucking...

90
00:08:32.596 --> 00:08:33.681
- [shattering]
- No!

91
00:08:37.935 --> 00:08:40.604
A hasty coronation.
a dragon escaping the pit.

92
00:08:40.688 --> 00:08:42.273
The people see an omen.

93
00:08:42.982 --> 00:08:47.278
They whisper in the streets.
They say perhaps Rhaenyra should be queen.

94
00:08:47.361 --> 00:08:51.532
And so you would name her:
Monster. Slayer of Infants.

95
00:08:52.408 --> 00:08:54.201
[Otto] I would do more than that.

96
00:08:55.202 --> 00:08:58.289
A funeral progress.
Let them see the child.

97
00:08:58.372 --> 00:09:02.418
Let them look upon the works
of this pretender to the throne.

98
00:09:05.004 --> 00:09:06.088
Father.

99
00:09:09.091 --> 00:09:10.885
- My king?
- No.

100
00:09:11.802 --> 00:09:15.347
I will not have my little son's body

101
00:09:15.431 --> 00:09:17.266
dragged through the street
like a dead dog.

102
00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:18.809
[Otto] Not dragged. honored!

103
00:09:19.935 --> 00:09:24.106
Escorted to the dragon pit
to be burned as a Targaryen prince!

104
00:09:25.316 --> 00:09:27.359
- Your Grace...
- No.

105
00:09:27.443 --> 00:09:29.445
[crying]

106
00:09:34.492 --> 00:09:37.036
Let no one say I do not grieve.

107
00:09:37.703 --> 00:09:42.833
Jaehaerys was my grandson. I loved him.
I will not have him die in vain.

108
00:09:44.084 --> 00:09:45.711
Those who declared for Rhaenyra.

109
00:09:45.795 --> 00:09:48.464
will they still support her
when they hear of her depravity?

110
00:09:48.547 --> 00:09:50.341
Or will they rather not renounce her?

111
00:09:52.760 --> 00:09:56.430
Jaehaerys will do more for us now
than a thousand knights in battle.

112
00:10:03.187 --> 00:10:05.189
You will have your war. Your Grace.

113
00:10:05.272 --> 00:10:09.819
But if you wait a short time.
you may yet double your strength.

114
00:10:12.446 --> 00:10:13.447
Mother?

115
00:10:18.911 --> 00:10:22.331
The Hand sets us on a difficult path.
my darling.

116
00:10:22.414 --> 00:10:24.208
But it might be the right one.

117
00:10:25.167 --> 00:10:29.213
Let the Silent Sisters ready the prince
for his final journey.

118
00:10:29.296 --> 00:10:32.508
And riding behind him.
his mother the queen.

119
00:10:32.591 --> 00:10:34.552
and with her. the queen dowager.

120
00:10:34.635 --> 00:10:36.303
No. I do not wish to be a spectacle.

121
00:10:36.387 --> 00:10:39.849
The realm must see
the sorrow of the crown.

122
00:10:39.932 --> 00:10:43.227
A sorrow best expressed
through its most gentle souls.

123
00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:51.318
I think you'll all agree
the king himself must be spared.

124
00:10:52.778 --> 00:10:54.655
- [waves lapping]
- [seagulls squawking]

125
00:11:01.453 --> 00:11:03.455
[footsteps approaching]

126
00:11:07.126 --> 00:11:09.169
[Alicent] There's to be a funeral
for Jaehaerys.

127
00:11:15.175 --> 00:11:17.595
We've been asked to ride
on a wagon behind his body.

128
00:11:23.767 --> 00:11:25.019
I don't want to.

129
00:11:26.770 --> 00:11:27.771
Neither do I.

130
00:11:30.441 --> 00:11:32.026
But when a thing like this happens...

131
00:11:33.819 --> 00:11:35.779
a blow to the king is a blow to the realm.

132
00:11:37.656 --> 00:11:39.074
When the people share our grief.

133
00:11:39.158 --> 00:11:41.452
- they draw closer to us.
- I don't want them closer.

134
00:11:42.328 --> 00:11:43.454
I don't know them.

135
00:11:45.289 --> 00:11:46.582
Sometimes we have to pretend.

136
00:11:49.543 --> 00:11:50.543
Why?

137
00:11:51.670 --> 00:11:54.131
We are representatives of the throne.
We have a duty.

138
00:11:57.176 --> 00:11:59.929
Helaena. what you saw last night
when you came to my room...

139
00:12:00.012 --> 00:12:01.513
This is for my boy.

140
00:12:10.731 --> 00:12:13.692
[solemn music playing]

141
00:12:13.776 --> 00:12:15.778
[indistinct chatter]

142
00:12:28.040 --> 00:12:30.042
[drum booming]

143
00:12:32.628 --> 00:12:34.046
[bell tolling]

144
00:13:13.043 --> 00:13:15.337
[panicked breathing]

145
00:13:16.422 --> 00:13:17.423
[clinking]

146
00:13:20.634 --> 00:13:23.554
I was... I was hired by Daemon Targaryen.

147
00:13:24.304 --> 00:13:27.391
He paid us half now.
half when the job is done.

148
00:13:27.474 --> 00:13:28.642
Who is "us"?

149
00:13:28.726 --> 00:13:32.938
A ratcatcher. Employed by the household.

150
00:13:33.022 --> 00:13:35.024
I don't know his right name.

151
00:13:35.107 --> 00:13:36.650
[bell tolling]

152
00:13:43.699 --> 00:13:49.788
Behold the works of Rhaenyra Targaryen!

153
00:13:52.791 --> 00:13:56.503
Pretender to the throne!

154
00:14:00.049 --> 00:14:01.467
Kinslayer!

155
00:14:02.051 --> 00:14:05.679
- [woman] Deepest sympathy. my queen.
- [man 1] Gods be with you. my queen.

156
00:14:05.763 --> 00:14:07.473
[man 2] We support you. Queen Helaena.

157
00:14:07.556 --> 00:14:11.310
[herald] Defiler of the innocent!

158
00:14:18.901 --> 00:14:24.156
[herald] Behold the works
of Rhaenyra the Cruel!

159
00:14:27.242 --> 00:14:28.577
[assassin] Are you gonna hurt me?

160
00:14:30.287 --> 00:14:31.455
No.

161
00:14:31.538 --> 00:14:33.332
[panicked breathing]

162
00:14:33.415 --> 00:14:34.958
But I cannot vouch for His Grace.

163
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:40.506
[tense music playing]

164
00:14:48.430 --> 00:14:49.556
[gasps]

165
00:14:52.601 --> 00:14:54.728
[breathing rapidly]

166
00:14:57.731 --> 00:15:00.234
[tense music continues playing]

167
00:15:00.317 --> 00:15:05.989
[herald] Behold the work
of Rhaenyra Targaryen!

168
00:15:06.073 --> 00:15:07.241
[woman 1] Our queen.

169
00:15:08.242 --> 00:15:11.954
[herald] Pretender to the throne!

170
00:15:15.124 --> 00:15:16.667
Kinslayer!

171
00:15:18.710 --> 00:15:22.464
Defiler of the innocent!

172
00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:27.302
[tense music continues]

173
00:15:36.895 --> 00:15:38.021
[woman 2] Queen Helaena!

174
00:15:38.105 --> 00:15:39.481
[breathing heavily]

175
00:15:41.650 --> 00:15:44.111
- [thudding]
- [horse neighs]

176
00:15:44.194 --> 00:15:45.571
[guard] What's happening there?

177
00:15:46.947 --> 00:15:48.115
[woman 3] Queen Helaena!

178
00:15:48.198 --> 00:15:49.926
- [soldier] What's going on?
- [leader] Move it. there!

179
00:15:49.950 --> 00:15:52.161
[indistinct chatter]

180
00:15:55.581 --> 00:15:58.167
- [woman 4] Queen Helaena.
- [woman 5] Queen Helaena!

181
00:15:58.250 --> 00:15:59.751
[crowd clamoring]

182
00:16:03.505 --> 00:16:05.591
- I'm so sorry.
- [woman 6] Queen Helaena!

183
00:16:06.216 --> 00:16:08.969
[crowd continues clamoring]

184
00:16:09.052 --> 00:16:10.804
- [woman 6] Queen Helaena!
- Helaena.

185
00:16:10.888 --> 00:16:14.224
- [man 1] Queen Helaena. Queen Helaena!
- [guard] Heave! Heave!

186
00:16:14.975 --> 00:16:15.975
[soldiers grunt]

187
00:16:16.393 --> 00:16:18.395
[crowd continues clamoring]

188
00:16:20.522 --> 00:16:21.732
[man 2] A curse!

189
00:16:21.815 --> 00:16:24.860
A curse on Rhaenyra. the Monstrous!

190
00:16:24.943 --> 00:16:26.945
[music intensifies]

191
00:16:28.363 --> 00:16:30.365
[music fades]

192
00:16:31.825 --> 00:16:35.746
[Gerardys] It is yet unclear
how the Keep itself was breached.

193
00:16:35.829 --> 00:16:41.210
The boy's head was severed from his body.
Thousands witnessed the procession.

194
00:16:42.252 --> 00:16:45.547
And they are accusing me
of having a hand in this?

195
00:16:45.631 --> 00:16:47.216
[Gerardys] It appears so.

196
00:16:47.299 --> 00:16:51.178
There have been messages sent
to that effect throughout the realm.

197
00:16:52.429 --> 00:16:56.308
We must send our own messages.
denying this vile allegation.

198
00:16:56.391 --> 00:17:00.437
I will do so at once. but I'm not sure
they will be received in good faith.

199
00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:03.857
And we must double our guard.
here and in Driftmark.

200
00:17:05.150 --> 00:17:07.378
There will be swift retribution.
in one form or another...

201
00:17:07.402 --> 00:17:09.196
I've seen to it. Your Grace.

202
00:17:10.572 --> 00:17:13.617
Let me fly out on Vermax.
Rhaenys is needed in the Gullet.

203
00:17:13.700 --> 00:17:15.345
I can watch for movements
from King's Landing.

204
00:17:15.369 --> 00:17:16.369
No.

205
00:17:18.247 --> 00:17:21.375
It must be said that the damage
to our position is immeasurable.

206
00:17:21.458 --> 00:17:24.419
at a time when we most need
loyalty to our cause.

207
00:17:25.921 --> 00:17:27.130
[Rhaenyra] But it's a lie.

208
00:17:28.674 --> 00:17:30.425
Having lost my own son...

209
00:17:31.635 --> 00:17:33.679
that I would inflict such a thing.

210
00:17:33.762 --> 00:17:35.347
On Helaena. of all people.

211
00:17:37.224 --> 00:17:38.225
An innocent.

212
00:17:44.856 --> 00:17:49.736
[Alfred] The death of Prince Lucerys
was a shock and an insult.

213
00:17:50.404 --> 00:17:52.155
A mother so aggrieved might...

214
00:17:52.990 --> 00:17:56.743
- naturally seek relief in retribution.
- Are you suggesting. Ser Alfred.

215
00:17:56.827 --> 00:17:59.955
that my grief drove me
to order the decapitation of a child?

216
00:18:00.038 --> 00:18:03.875
I merely thought. perhaps.
an action taken in haste...

217
00:18:03.959 --> 00:18:05.335
Mind yourself.

218
00:18:15.470 --> 00:18:16.470
[sighs]

219
00:18:24.396 --> 00:18:28.150
Did you send assassins
to murder children in their beds?

220
00:18:28.233 --> 00:18:31.445
- I sent the queen's vengeance for her son.
- What did you tell this vengeance?

221
00:18:31.528 --> 00:18:33.655
What did you say to him. Daemon.

222
00:18:33.739 --> 00:18:35.779
that a boy lies dead
and I am accused of killing it?

223
00:18:35.824 --> 00:18:38.076
Mysaria provided me with names
and a subterfuge.

224
00:18:38.160 --> 00:18:43.081
I was clear in my instructions:
Aemond. the brother of Aegon the Usurper.

225
00:18:43.165 --> 00:18:45.751
- I cannot be responsible for a mistake.
- Cannot be responsible?

226
00:18:51.381 --> 00:18:55.510
If Aemond was not to be found.
what were your instructions then?

227
00:18:55.594 --> 00:18:58.096
They did not concern in any way
that of a little child.

228
00:18:58.180 --> 00:19:00.724
You said that it was your aim
to spill Hightower blood.

229
00:19:00.807 --> 00:19:02.809
and if not Aemond. then anyone would do.

230
00:19:02.893 --> 00:19:05.103
- No.
- You have wounded me.

231
00:19:05.187 --> 00:19:08.940
Weakened my claim to the throne.
my ability to raise an army.

232
00:19:09.024 --> 00:19:11.276
my standing among my own council.

233
00:19:11.360 --> 00:19:13.612
I said. no.

234
00:19:13.695 --> 00:19:14.946
I don't believe you.

235
00:19:26.875 --> 00:19:28.710
So we come to it at long last.

236
00:19:30.003 --> 00:19:31.088
[Rhaenyra sighs]

237
00:19:34.174 --> 00:19:35.550
I cannot trust you. Daemon.

238
00:19:38.095 --> 00:19:43.058
I've never trusted you wholly.
much though I wished to. Willed myself to.

239
00:19:44.935 --> 00:19:47.437
But now I have seen
that your heart belongs only to you.

240
00:19:48.146 --> 00:19:51.149
And when I was a child.
I took this as a challenge.

241
00:19:51.233 --> 00:19:53.735
But I'm older now.
I have challenges enough.

242
00:19:53.819 --> 00:19:55.904
- I have served you faithfully.
- Have you?

243
00:19:55.987 --> 00:20:01.451
Or have you used me as a tool with which
to grasp at your stolen inheritance?

244
00:20:02.869 --> 00:20:03.869
[gasps]

245
00:20:10.460 --> 00:20:11.837
[breathing shakily]

246
00:20:19.761 --> 00:20:24.933
When Ser Erryk brought you the crown.
did I myself not place it upon your brow?

247
00:20:25.016 --> 00:20:27.060
Yes. but before that.

248
00:20:27.144 --> 00:20:32.274
you sought to lead a council of war
while I labored alone in my bedchamber.

249
00:20:32.357 --> 00:20:35.735
And afterward. when I thought it meet
to consider terms our foes put before us...

250
00:20:35.819 --> 00:20:39.406
A folly! To give up my brother's throne
to the traitorous lies of Otto Hightower...

251
00:20:39.489 --> 00:20:42.367
My throne. Daemon. Mine!

252
00:20:42.993 --> 00:20:47.122
I think you used my words as an excuse.
To take your own revenge.

253
00:20:48.331 --> 00:20:51.710
To indulge the darkness
you keep sheathed within you like a blade.

254
00:20:51.793 --> 00:20:54.439
- You think me some kind of monster.
- I don't know what to think of you.

255
00:20:54.463 --> 00:20:57.007
I don't know what you are.
Or who it is you serve.

256
00:20:57.090 --> 00:21:02.304
Am I not on way even now to Harrenhal
to raise an army in your name. Rhaenyra?

257
00:21:02.387 --> 00:21:03.722
Yours!

258
00:21:11.521 --> 00:21:15.692
Do you accept me as your queen and ruler?

259
00:21:19.029 --> 00:21:21.573
Or do you cling even now
to what you think you lost?

260
00:21:24.743 --> 00:21:26.536
What I think I lost?

261
00:21:26.620 --> 00:21:28.497
You did not lose it. you gave it away.

262
00:21:29.331 --> 00:21:30.999
Because you thought ever and only

263
00:21:31.082 --> 00:21:34.169
of your own glory. and not of my father.
in his grief. who needed you!

264
00:21:34.252 --> 00:21:37.339
Your father was a coward
who knew I was the stronger son.

265
00:21:37.422 --> 00:21:40.550
that I was the leader of men.
and he was afraid to be seen in my shadow.

266
00:21:40.634 --> 00:21:42.195
Is that what you understand
of your own brother?

267
00:21:42.219 --> 00:21:44.554
You know him better than I do.
who was raised at his side?

268
00:21:44.638 --> 00:21:47.516
Do you believe he made you heir
because of your great wisdom.

269
00:21:47.599 --> 00:21:48.767
because of your virtue?

270
00:21:49.768 --> 00:21:52.270
- How dare you.
- Or did he merely use you as a tool

271
00:21:52.354 --> 00:21:55.565
to put me in my place
because he was afraid of me?

272
00:21:55.649 --> 00:21:58.527
Because he knew your legacy. unlike mine.
would never outshine his own?

273
00:21:58.610 --> 00:22:01.613
He was not afraid of you. Daemon!

274
00:22:02.531 --> 00:22:04.950
He could not trust you.

275
00:22:05.742 --> 00:22:08.411
- Any more than I can trust you.
- He was a fool.

276
00:22:09.746 --> 00:22:12.457
Who sought greatness. but shrank
from spilling blood to achieve it.

277
00:22:12.541 --> 00:22:14.334
And I see you will suffer the same fate.

278
00:22:15.919 --> 00:22:17.712
You struck down a child.

279
00:22:21.800 --> 00:22:23.301
It was a mistake.

280
00:22:28.390 --> 00:22:29.474
You're pathetic.

281
00:22:39.568 --> 00:22:40.777
[sighs]

282
00:22:51.413 --> 00:22:52.539
[door slams]

283
00:23:05.510 --> 00:23:06.511
Father?

284
00:23:16.062 --> 00:23:17.772
You wished to see me. Your Grace?

285
00:23:27.407 --> 00:23:28.992
When morning comes.

286
00:23:29.117 --> 00:23:32.537
take Moondancer
and keep a watch on King's Landing.

287
00:23:33.455 --> 00:23:35.206
I must know which course they take next.

288
00:23:35.874 --> 00:23:36.916
I will be vigilant.

289
00:23:38.209 --> 00:23:39.628
I depend on you. Baela.

290
00:23:40.837 --> 00:23:43.006
Stay high and keep your distance.

291
00:23:44.549 --> 00:23:46.301
We can afford no further mistakes.

292
00:23:56.728 --> 00:23:57.729
My father?

293
00:24:02.317 --> 00:24:03.818
He must follow his own path.

294
00:24:14.287 --> 00:24:16.247
[tense music playing]

295
00:24:20.418 --> 00:24:24.339
[screeching. then growling]

296
00:24:42.399 --> 00:24:44.234
[dramatic music playing]

297
00:25:00.792 --> 00:25:02.794
[birds chirping]

298
00:25:03.586 --> 00:25:05.588
[music turns poignant]

299
00:25:56.931 --> 00:25:58.266
If it please. my lord.

300
00:27:23.101 --> 00:27:24.227
Have you told anyone?

301
00:27:27.939 --> 00:27:29.941
[softly] What do you take me for?

302
00:27:32.068 --> 00:27:33.820
[softly] One who seeks absolution.

303
00:27:35.154 --> 00:27:36.823
There is none for what I've done.

304
00:27:49.377 --> 00:27:51.379
[poignant music playing]

305
00:29:14.504 --> 00:29:15.713
What is this?

306
00:29:19.342 --> 00:29:21.511
It's a reminder of yesterday. I think.

307
00:29:22.178 --> 00:29:24.847
The procession was muddy.
I'll replace it hence.

308
00:29:24.931 --> 00:29:25.931
Do it now.

309
00:29:29.102 --> 00:29:31.980
The night was long. Ser Criston.
I have not eaten. If I could just...

310
00:29:32.063 --> 00:29:34.023
You defy my authority. Ser Arryk.

311
00:29:36.317 --> 00:29:37.360
I do not.

312
00:29:37.443 --> 00:29:40.196
The white cloak is a symbol of our purity.

313
00:29:40.989 --> 00:29:41.990
Our fidelity.

314
00:29:43.116 --> 00:29:44.909
The Kingsguard are a sacred trust.

315
00:29:45.576 --> 00:29:48.705
Will you so easily sully
our ancient honor?

316
00:30:02.218 --> 00:30:04.178
I have erred. my lord.

317
00:30:05.680 --> 00:30:06.806
I'll remedy the error.

318
00:30:12.645 --> 00:30:14.439
Where were you
when Jaehaerys was murdered?

319
00:30:19.610 --> 00:30:20.610
With King Aegon.

320
00:30:22.280 --> 00:30:26.034
Then you were not in the private quarters
where you might've prevented the crime.

321
00:30:26.117 --> 00:30:29.328
His Grace wished to entertain
his companions in the throne room.

322
00:30:29.412 --> 00:30:32.623
- Well. if you'd thought to go upstairs...
- Where were you. Lord Commander?

323
00:30:34.250 --> 00:30:36.794
Why has Helaena. the queen.
been granted no sworn protector?

324
00:30:36.878 --> 00:30:38.212
Surely once she ascended...

325
00:30:38.296 --> 00:30:41.174
Your brother is a thief
and a traitor to the crown!

326
00:30:50.308 --> 00:30:51.768
You well know how it pains me.

327
00:30:51.851 --> 00:30:54.395
How are we to know
you do not secretly share his sentiments?

328
00:30:54.479 --> 00:30:56.272
I denounced him before the king.

329
00:30:56.355 --> 00:30:58.733
We were one soul in two bodies. yes.

330
00:30:59.567 --> 00:31:02.028
If I'd shared his sentiments.
I would have fled with him.

331
00:31:04.197 --> 00:31:06.240
First. your brother betrays us.

332
00:31:07.075 --> 00:31:08.618
[laughs]

333
00:31:09.243 --> 00:31:10.953
And then the young prince...

334
00:31:12.330 --> 00:31:15.666
is murdered on your watch.

335
00:31:15.750 --> 00:31:18.544
You are mad. Ser. Mad.
You cannot think that I did this!

336
00:31:18.628 --> 00:31:20.838
What I think has no relevance!

337
00:31:24.592 --> 00:31:26.677
You have brought disgrace upon our ranks.

338
00:31:30.515 --> 00:31:32.308
And now you must restore it.

339
00:31:34.352 --> 00:31:35.686
How am I to do that?

340
00:31:35.770 --> 00:31:36.854
[metal clattering]

341
00:31:52.411 --> 00:31:56.791
You will go to Dragonstone
and strike down Rhaenyra in her own halls.

342
00:31:58.668 --> 00:32:00.503
The way she sought to do with Aemond.

343
00:32:01.129 --> 00:32:04.090
We will pay the princess back
in her own bloody coin.

344
00:32:06.259 --> 00:32:09.137
- Alone?
- Does your courage fail you. Ser Arryk?

345
00:32:09.220 --> 00:32:10.847
It's not a matter of courage.

346
00:32:10.930 --> 00:32:14.058
The castle is defended
against all enemies. now especially.

347
00:32:15.768 --> 00:32:16.811
How would I enter?

348
00:32:16.894 --> 00:32:19.334
Your twin serves there
at the pleasure of the so-called queen.

349
00:32:19.397 --> 00:32:21.566
They will mistake you for him
if you play the part.

350
00:32:22.650 --> 00:32:26.445
We are sworn to serve forthrightly.
not to traffic in deception.

351
00:32:26.529 --> 00:32:30.867
Put down the pretender
and you will end a war before it begins.

352
00:32:38.916 --> 00:32:41.061
- If they see the two of us...
- You must not let that happen.

353
00:32:41.085 --> 00:32:43.504
- You would send me to my death.
- Or to triumph.

354
00:32:46.299 --> 00:32:47.675
[softly] And glory.

355
00:32:53.639 --> 00:32:54.974
Now. will you go?

356
00:32:56.767 --> 00:32:59.604
Or must I question your loyalty
to the king?

357
00:33:05.401 --> 00:33:06.527
As you command...

358
00:33:07.737 --> 00:33:08.737
my lord.

359
00:33:16.162 --> 00:33:17.705
[arrow thunks]

360
00:33:18.831 --> 00:33:19.999
You missed supper.

361
00:33:21.375 --> 00:33:22.835
I wasn't hungry.

362
00:33:22.919 --> 00:33:24.712
I don't think anyone was. really.

363
00:33:25.880 --> 00:33:27.256
Too many empty seats.

364
00:33:29.175 --> 00:33:30.343
Do you know where he went?

365
00:33:31.510 --> 00:33:33.095
Harrenhal. I would think.

366
00:33:37.683 --> 00:33:39.268
Sometimes I think I hate him.

367
00:33:43.439 --> 00:33:46.275
It's hard. with fathers.

368
00:33:47.360 --> 00:33:49.320
[Baela] What do you remember of my uncle?

369
00:33:50.488 --> 00:33:52.114
[Jace] He taught us to catch fish.

370
00:33:53.991 --> 00:33:56.702
And sing sailors' shanties.

371
00:33:57.578 --> 00:33:59.205
He had a weakness for cake.

372
00:34:01.499 --> 00:34:02.500
And...

373
00:34:03.542 --> 00:34:04.877
Ser Harwin Strong?

374
00:34:07.296 --> 00:34:10.216
He was gentle. And fierce.

375
00:34:13.469 --> 00:34:15.972
They called him Breakbones.

376
00:34:19.141 --> 00:34:21.435
He loved us. I think.

377
00:34:23.437 --> 00:34:24.522
Of course he did.

378
00:34:27.024 --> 00:34:29.068
[breathes deeply]

379
00:34:30.778 --> 00:34:31.862
I miss Luke.

380
00:34:37.034 --> 00:34:39.036
[sensual music playing]

381
00:34:40.121 --> 00:34:42.248
[indistinct chatter]

382
00:35:13.571 --> 00:35:15.448
Daemon sent them to kill me.

383
00:35:18.242 --> 00:35:19.327
I was out.

384
00:35:20.703 --> 00:35:22.121
You were with me.

385
00:35:22.997 --> 00:35:24.540
In truth. I am proud...

386
00:35:26.000 --> 00:35:28.044
that he considers me such a foe...

387
00:35:30.296 --> 00:35:32.757
and that he seeks to murder me in my bed.

388
00:35:33.883 --> 00:35:35.134
He's afraid of me.

389
00:35:36.510 --> 00:35:37.928
As well he should be.

390
00:35:39.722 --> 00:35:41.932
The boy is grown into a man.

391
00:35:42.016 --> 00:35:44.226
[grunts] No. Not here.

392
00:35:54.987 --> 00:35:57.198
I do regret that business with Luke.

393
00:35:58.616 --> 00:36:02.119
I lost my temper that day.
I am sorry for it.

394
00:36:03.120 --> 00:36:04.705
I am glad to hear it.

395
00:36:07.917 --> 00:36:10.211
They used to tease me. you know.

396
00:36:12.963 --> 00:36:14.382
Because I was different.

397
00:36:17.593 --> 00:36:21.472
I would remind you only that
when princes lose their temper.

398
00:36:21.555 --> 00:36:23.391
it is often others who suffer.

399
00:36:27.144 --> 00:36:28.479
The smallfolk.

400
00:36:29.688 --> 00:36:30.689
Like me.

401
00:36:35.611 --> 00:36:36.862
[Hugh] <i>How is she?</i>

402
00:36:36.946 --> 00:36:38.823
- [girl coughs]
- [Kat] Much the same.

403
00:36:42.618 --> 00:36:43.618
[coughs]

404
00:36:51.127 --> 00:36:53.379
The markets have been running low
since the blockade.

405
00:36:54.547 --> 00:36:56.757
Surely the city cannot yet
be short of food.

406
00:36:57.675 --> 00:37:00.136
I think not. but people are afraid.

407
00:37:00.845 --> 00:37:02.972
Those with means are hoarding
everything they can.

408
00:37:05.933 --> 00:37:08.269
I walked two hours today
to find a chicken for the pot.

409
00:37:09.437 --> 00:37:11.355
And paid three times as much
as I should have.

410
00:37:13.691 --> 00:37:16.152
[girl coughing]

411
00:37:23.117 --> 00:37:24.410
[girl coughing]

412
00:37:26.287 --> 00:37:27.663
The selfishness of people.

413
00:37:28.789 --> 00:37:32.460
I cannot blame anyone for doing
what I myself would do if I could.

414
00:37:32.543 --> 00:37:35.583
I don't think you'd let children go hungry
while you filled your own cellars.

415
00:37:36.589 --> 00:37:38.632
Lucky we don't have enough coin
to find out.

416
00:37:39.550 --> 00:37:40.968
[girl coughs]

417
00:37:41.051 --> 00:37:43.387
The king has promised us some relief.

418
00:37:43.471 --> 00:37:44.763
[girl moans]

419
00:37:45.723 --> 00:37:46.724
Did he say when?

420
00:37:54.190 --> 00:37:55.399
I'm afraid. Hugh.

421
00:37:55.483 --> 00:37:57.318
[girl coughing]

422
00:37:59.612 --> 00:38:01.447
[indistinct chatter]

423
00:38:05.868 --> 00:38:09.455
I see all your great adventures
have done nothing for your looks.

424
00:38:11.457 --> 00:38:12.458
[chuckles]

425
00:38:13.209 --> 00:38:15.961
Well met. brother.
After many months away.

426
00:38:26.263 --> 00:38:27.515
I missed you.

427
00:38:28.599 --> 00:38:29.599
[chuckles]

428
00:38:29.642 --> 00:38:32.561
- Did you slay many pirates?
- Oh. more than you. to be sure.

429
00:38:32.645 --> 00:38:36.649
Ha. A jest. One you may regret
as you're supping alone tonight.

430
00:38:37.483 --> 00:38:41.278
I regret it already.
I've broken my teeth on hard tack. Addam.

431
00:38:41.362 --> 00:38:45.032
Say you have a pot of your goat stew
simmering at home.

432
00:38:45.115 --> 00:38:46.116
You're in luck.

433
00:38:47.284 --> 00:38:48.827
In more ways than one.

434
00:38:49.745 --> 00:38:53.582
I hear Lord Corlys himself
commended you for your service to him.

435
00:38:56.126 --> 00:38:58.337
- He did.
- Will you sail with him?

436
00:38:58.420 --> 00:38:59.964
When his ship has been repaired.

437
00:39:01.215 --> 00:39:03.717
I am one of a dozen shipwrights
now called from Hull

438
00:39:03.801 --> 00:39:05.386
to attend with all speed to your fleet.

439
00:39:06.845 --> 00:39:07.845
He made no offer.

440
00:39:09.682 --> 00:39:13.435
- And I'd rather he didn't. truth be told.
- Do not be foolish. Alyn.

441
00:39:15.604 --> 00:39:18.649
To serve with the Sea Snake
is to make your fortune.

442
00:39:18.732 --> 00:39:20.901
Had I such a chance. I would leap at it.

443
00:39:20.985 --> 00:39:23.112
That's because you haven't seen
what I have seen.

444
00:39:23.195 --> 00:39:26.824
There is a war brewing. Addam.
A real one.

445
00:39:26.907 --> 00:39:29.827
Another opportunity
to distinguish yourself.

446
00:39:29.910 --> 00:39:32.329
- Remind him of your worth.
- Oh. I need no favors.

447
00:39:32.413 --> 00:39:35.207
But. brother. he owes you. He owes us.

448
00:39:37.626 --> 00:39:39.086
Does the stew have carrots in it?

449
00:39:40.254 --> 00:39:41.380
[chuckles]

450
00:39:41.463 --> 00:39:43.465
[seagulls squawking]

451
00:39:44.925 --> 00:39:46.594
I mistrust this silence.

452
00:39:48.429 --> 00:39:51.140
Daemon flies
when we most need his hand at the oar.

453
00:39:53.142 --> 00:39:55.769
Devotion has never sat well with him.

454
00:39:55.853 --> 00:39:59.940
Where he goes.
he wishes to be his own master.

455
00:40:02.359 --> 00:40:04.278
Well. he is the king consort.

456
00:40:07.948 --> 00:40:10.284
But he is not the king.

457
00:40:11.243 --> 00:40:13.495
Neither am I. But I manage.

458
00:40:16.874 --> 00:40:21.545
I too have felt the crown pass over me.
It is a hard thing to accept.

459
00:40:24.340 --> 00:40:27.426
And now Viserys is dead
and all claims are in doubt.

460
00:40:28.552 --> 00:40:32.139
You don't think Daemon will challenge her?

461
00:40:34.266 --> 00:40:35.476
Not as such.

462
00:40:39.897 --> 00:40:42.232
But neither can he allow her
to command him.

463
00:40:42.983 --> 00:40:43.984
Pity.

464
00:40:44.985 --> 00:40:49.073
I have. on occasion.
found that to be quite enjoyable.

465
00:40:49.823 --> 00:40:51.158
[chuckles]

466
00:40:54.036 --> 00:40:56.038
Well. let us take him at his word.

467
00:40:57.623 --> 00:41:00.626
And if he can take Harrenhal.
all may well be forgiven.

468
00:41:01.710 --> 00:41:03.337
In the meantime. I am here.

469
00:41:05.506 --> 00:41:06.590
And Meleys.

470
00:41:06.674 --> 00:41:09.510
[breathes deeply]

471
00:41:10.344 --> 00:41:12.513
We will not let the queen falter.

472
00:41:15.474 --> 00:41:17.476
[poignant music playing]

473
00:41:36.120 --> 00:41:37.329
[footsteps approaching]

474
00:41:41.834 --> 00:41:44.128
The lady Mysaria. Your Grace.

475
00:41:55.597 --> 00:41:58.183
You're aware of yesterday's events
in King's Landing?

476
00:42:00.269 --> 00:42:01.478
I am.

477
00:42:02.354 --> 00:42:04.398
Tell me what part you played
in their unfolding.

478
00:42:04.481 --> 00:42:06.275
I had nothing to do with it.

479
00:42:06.358 --> 00:42:08.777
I know you are entwined with the usurpers.

480
00:42:08.861 --> 00:42:11.196
That you aided them
in denying me my birthright.

481
00:42:11.280 --> 00:42:15.409
I took profit from an inevitability.
I regret it now.

482
00:42:15.951 --> 00:42:16.952
I'm sure you do.

483
00:42:20.372 --> 00:42:21.372
Who are you?

484
00:42:23.167 --> 00:42:24.209
A prisoner.

485
00:42:36.638 --> 00:42:38.807
I gave Daemon two names.

486
00:42:38.891 --> 00:42:42.770
That is the extent of it.
And I did not wish to do that much.

487
00:42:43.687 --> 00:42:45.355
He said it was the price of my freedom.

488
00:42:54.490 --> 00:42:55.949
Does he say otherwise?

489
00:42:57.075 --> 00:42:58.076
He is gone.

490
00:43:00.329 --> 00:43:01.330
For how long?

491
00:43:02.998 --> 00:43:05.834
A week. Or forever. I do not know.

492
00:43:11.465 --> 00:43:12.925
He does do that.

493
00:43:14.218 --> 00:43:15.219
Doesn't he?

494
00:43:24.561 --> 00:43:25.979
You remember me now.

495
00:43:30.526 --> 00:43:31.819
He said he would marry you.

496
00:43:34.404 --> 00:43:38.242
- He said you carried his child.
- Not everyone found the jest funny.

497
00:43:38.784 --> 00:43:42.162
And now it seems he's done it again.
Made a promise and then...

498
00:43:42.955 --> 00:43:46.208
- slipped away.
- You trade in the secrets of the Red Keep.

499
00:43:47.334 --> 00:43:51.088
Your web runs unseen
through King's Landing. And now...

500
00:43:51.755 --> 00:43:54.091
when my enemy coils himself
to strike at me...

501
00:43:54.174 --> 00:43:58.595
I can do nothing now but ask you
to honor your husband's words.

502
00:43:58.679 --> 00:44:00.931
It would not serve me to set you free.

503
00:44:03.809 --> 00:44:06.979
At best. I lose an asset to my cause.

504
00:44:09.523 --> 00:44:11.441
At worst. you betray me
in some fouler way.

505
00:44:11.525 --> 00:44:14.486
I have no interest in betraying you.
Your Grace.

506
00:44:16.864 --> 00:44:17.864
So you say.

507
00:44:27.082 --> 00:44:29.751
I was brought to Westeros with nothing.

508
00:44:29.835 --> 00:44:32.546
I toiled in service. I stole.

509
00:44:32.629 --> 00:44:35.132
I sold my own body for coin or bread.

510
00:44:35.757 --> 00:44:37.968
And I listened.

511
00:44:38.051 --> 00:44:39.928
I collected confidences.

512
00:44:40.012 --> 00:44:42.431
I made myself valuable to powerful men.

513
00:44:42.514 --> 00:44:44.808
Bit by bit. I earned my living.

514
00:44:44.892 --> 00:44:46.727
A house. A household.

515
00:44:46.810 --> 00:44:47.936
A home.

516
00:44:49.021 --> 00:44:50.689
Then they set it all aflame.

517
00:44:52.441 --> 00:44:55.944
- Who did?
- The Hightowers. I can only assume.

518
00:44:57.321 --> 00:45:01.909
The Hand did not like it
when I showed my teeth.

519
00:45:03.660 --> 00:45:05.245
But I thank him for it.

520
00:45:06.079 --> 00:45:11.126
For too long. I made it my aim
to be of consequence.

521
00:45:11.209 --> 00:45:15.714
But now I see
that was the wish of a child.

522
00:45:16.423 --> 00:45:17.549
Daemon...

523
00:45:18.383 --> 00:45:20.135
Otto Hightower...

524
00:45:20.719 --> 00:45:22.346
Makes no difference.

525
00:45:22.429 --> 00:45:24.806
They will never accept me.

526
00:45:25.515 --> 00:45:27.517
I might as well have remained a whore.

527
00:45:34.191 --> 00:45:35.484
How did you get that scar?

528
00:45:59.341 --> 00:46:00.968
[seagulls squawking]

529
00:46:20.195 --> 00:46:22.447
[dragon screeches]

530
00:46:22.531 --> 00:46:24.700
[suspenseful music playing]

531
00:46:32.416 --> 00:46:34.376
[screeching]

532
00:46:52.936 --> 00:46:54.813
[indistinct chatter]

533
00:47:11.747 --> 00:47:13.749
[woman wailing]

534
00:47:13.832 --> 00:47:15.500
[tense music playing]

535
00:47:15.584 --> 00:47:16.585
Oh. no.

536
00:47:17.919 --> 00:47:19.046
My son.

537
00:47:21.381 --> 00:47:22.841
[woman wailing]

538
00:47:24.301 --> 00:47:26.303
[wailing]

539
00:47:35.812 --> 00:47:38.482
- Who are they?
- Ratcatchers.

540
00:47:39.858 --> 00:47:41.401
In the king's employ.

541
00:47:43.570 --> 00:47:44.571
What'd they do?

542
00:47:57.334 --> 00:47:59.795
[whimpering]

543
00:48:12.891 --> 00:48:14.017
What have you done?

544
00:48:18.855 --> 00:48:20.816
The ratcatchers!

545
00:48:21.983 --> 00:48:22.983
Oh.

546
00:48:23.610 --> 00:48:25.153
I had them hanged.

547
00:48:27.906 --> 00:48:30.951
The maggot who took my son
confessed to an accomplice.

548
00:48:31.785 --> 00:48:33.787
He could not say for certain
which man it was.

549
00:48:33.870 --> 00:48:35.163
- So...
- Idiot!

550
00:48:35.247 --> 00:48:37.457
Beware how you speak to your king.
my lord.

551
00:48:37.541 --> 00:48:41.837
The king is my grandson.
and my grandson is a fool!

552
00:48:41.920 --> 00:48:45.423
He's worse than a fool.
He's murdered innocent men!

553
00:48:45.507 --> 00:48:46.842
And one guilty one.

554
00:48:46.925 --> 00:48:49.928
And hanged them from the walls of the city
for all to see!

555
00:48:50.011 --> 00:48:52.406
Plot against the king
and I will pay it back a hundred times.

556
00:48:52.430 --> 00:48:54.766
They are fathers and brothers and sons!

557
00:48:55.642 --> 00:48:58.353
And their wives and children
gather now at our gates

558
00:48:58.436 --> 00:49:00.730
to weep and curse your name!

559
00:49:12.659 --> 00:49:16.788
With your child's blood.
we bought their approval.

560
00:49:16.872 --> 00:49:18.165
With your mother's tears.

561
00:49:18.248 --> 00:49:22.169
we made a bitter sacrifice
against the deprivations to come.

562
00:49:22.252 --> 00:49:24.087
And you've thrown it away.

563
00:49:25.672 --> 00:49:27.215
After all I've done for you.

564
00:49:27.299 --> 00:49:28.466
Thoughtless.

565
00:49:29.050 --> 00:49:30.343
Feckless.

566
00:49:32.095 --> 00:49:33.221
Self-indulgent.

567
00:49:33.305 --> 00:49:34.723
At least I did something.

568
00:49:34.806 --> 00:49:38.185
I have not answered
injury to the crown with what?

569
00:49:38.268 --> 00:49:41.730
Wailing? Currying favor
with the fishwives?

570
00:49:41.813 --> 00:49:44.357
- I will not be thought weak.
- [Otto] Even now.

571
00:49:44.441 --> 00:49:47.152
news of Rhaenyra's monstrous crime
spreads through the realm.

572
00:49:47.235 --> 00:49:50.822
The great houses falter.
They cannot but come to our side.

573
00:49:50.906 --> 00:49:53.074
I wish to spill blood. not ink.

574
00:49:54.159 --> 00:49:55.493
We must act.

575
00:49:56.786 --> 00:49:58.455
Ser Cristin Cole has acted.

576
00:50:07.756 --> 00:50:09.174
And what...

577
00:50:10.550 --> 00:50:13.345
has Ser Cristin Cole done?

578
00:50:15.096 --> 00:50:17.641
He has sent Ser Arryk to slay Rhaenyra.

579
00:50:23.104 --> 00:50:24.105
Alone?

580
00:50:26.775 --> 00:50:29.027
He's pretending
to be his own twin. Brilliant.

581
00:50:33.990 --> 00:50:35.533
Gods help us all.

582
00:50:36.451 --> 00:50:38.787
It's time the Bitch Queen paid a price.

583
00:50:42.415 --> 00:50:47.671
And you acceded to this... This prank
without consulting me?

584
00:50:47.754 --> 00:50:48.964
Or the council?

585
00:50:49.798 --> 00:50:52.884
Instead of judgment.
you display impetuousness

586
00:50:52.968 --> 00:50:55.971
and diminish us in the eyes of our enemy!

587
00:50:56.054 --> 00:50:58.390
Ill-considered. trifling...

588
00:51:09.276 --> 00:51:11.319
Do you never think of your father?

589
00:51:11.903 --> 00:51:12.904
His...

590
00:51:14.281 --> 00:51:18.702
forbearance. his judiciousness. his...

591
00:51:22.330 --> 00:51:24.499
His dignity?

592
00:51:24.582 --> 00:51:26.293
[Aegon] Fuck dignity.

593
00:51:27.002 --> 00:51:28.378
I want revenge.

594
00:51:31.172 --> 00:51:32.549
My father is dead.

595
00:51:35.510 --> 00:51:36.594
He is.

596
00:51:38.805 --> 00:51:41.057
And we are the poorer for it.

597
00:51:56.573 --> 00:51:58.366
He was right about you.

598
00:52:01.453 --> 00:52:02.579
He made me king.

599
00:52:03.538 --> 00:52:06.166
[laughing]

600
00:52:07.834 --> 00:52:09.711
Is that what you think?

601
00:52:16.593 --> 00:52:19.012
[Aegon] Remove your badge. Ser Otto.

602
00:52:27.354 --> 00:52:28.980
You were my father's Hand...

603
00:52:30.523 --> 00:52:31.775
not mine.

604
00:52:33.193 --> 00:52:34.194
Take it off.

605
00:52:36.863 --> 00:52:38.323
You wouldn't dare.

606
00:52:38.865 --> 00:52:41.284
[chuckling]

607
00:52:41.785 --> 00:52:42.952
I have dared.

608
00:52:44.287 --> 00:52:46.081
And I find it stimulating.

609
00:52:56.424 --> 00:52:58.385
Insolent pup.

610
00:53:02.389 --> 00:53:07.185
You think yourself clever.
but without a strong Hand at your side...

611
00:53:10.563 --> 00:53:11.731
to guide...

612
00:53:15.527 --> 00:53:16.778
Give it to Cole.

613
00:53:21.699 --> 00:53:22.700
Your Grace?

614
00:53:27.455 --> 00:53:32.335
In this hour. you have proven yourself
of more worth than a hundred old men.

615
00:53:36.339 --> 00:53:40.176
My new Hand will be a steel fist.

616
00:53:41.511 --> 00:53:45.723
You will regret this.

617
00:53:47.767 --> 00:53:48.768
Give it to him.

618
00:54:07.245 --> 00:54:08.455
You are dismissed.

619
00:54:18.131 --> 00:54:19.215
[door closes]

620
00:54:19.799 --> 00:54:21.509
[Rhaenyra] <i>I do not know if I trust you.</i>

621
00:54:22.218 --> 00:54:25.305
And I sense
that there is danger in you yet.

622
00:54:27.599 --> 00:54:30.477
But I will keep the word of my house
if you say that it was given.

623
00:54:38.943 --> 00:54:39.944
You may go.

624
00:54:41.446 --> 00:54:42.780
Your Grace.

625
00:54:42.864 --> 00:54:46.367
[Rhaenyra] There's a Velaryon ship in the
harbor. bound for Myr by way of Pentos.

626
00:54:46.451 --> 00:54:48.077
I will see that you are given passage.

627
00:54:49.120 --> 00:54:51.289
I'm not so unworldly
as to let you fly free.

628
00:54:51.372 --> 00:54:52.499
I am...

629
00:54:53.750 --> 00:54:54.751
Thank you.

630
00:54:57.754 --> 00:54:59.881
Ser Erryk. Mysaria will be leaving us.

631
00:54:59.964 --> 00:55:01.716
Let her collect her things.

632
00:55:01.799 --> 00:55:04.594
then have someone take her down
and secure her berth on the <i>Corwyn.</i>

633
00:55:05.220 --> 00:55:06.346
Your Grace.

634
00:55:09.349 --> 00:55:12.227
[poignant music playing]

635
00:55:14.854 --> 00:55:16.856
[seagulls squawking]

636
00:55:28.618 --> 00:55:29.953
[exhales]

637
00:55:41.381 --> 00:55:43.383
[music turns tense]

638
00:55:52.433 --> 00:55:53.434
A moment?

639
00:56:23.464 --> 00:56:24.799
[guard] Ser Erryk.

640
00:56:25.967 --> 00:56:28.928
- I thought you were within.
- A sorry lack of vigilance.

641
00:56:29.929 --> 00:56:31.556
The enemy is about. good Ser.

642
00:56:42.317 --> 00:56:43.860
[door closes]

643
00:56:43.943 --> 00:56:45.945
[suspenseful music playing]

644
00:58:33.219 --> 00:58:35.096
[Elinda] Please try and lay down.
Your Grace.

645
00:58:35.722 --> 00:58:37.014
[Rhaenyra] Thank you. Elinda.

646
00:59:01.330 --> 00:59:02.331
Ser Erryk.

647
00:59:04.792 --> 00:59:06.127
It has been a strange day.

648
00:59:07.420 --> 00:59:10.298
I'm restless.
I will stand this evening's duty.

649
00:59:14.135 --> 00:59:16.137
[tense music playing]

650
00:59:24.145 --> 00:59:28.357
You must sleep tonight. Your Grace.
Let me ask the maester for a draught.

651
00:59:29.192 --> 00:59:30.193
Perhaps it would be best.

652
00:59:32.904 --> 00:59:33.905
Thank you. Elinda.

653
00:59:41.370 --> 00:59:42.371
[door opens]

654
00:59:45.583 --> 00:59:46.584
Ser Erryk.

655
00:59:54.717 --> 00:59:58.054
Believe me. I had no choice.

656
00:59:58.137 --> 00:59:59.180
I don't understand.

657
00:59:59.931 --> 01:00:00.932
Brother!

658
01:00:03.935 --> 01:00:05.186
Do not do this.

659
01:00:06.187 --> 01:00:07.396
I beg you.

660
01:00:09.565 --> 01:00:11.609
You are the one who betrayed us. Erryk.

661
01:00:11.692 --> 01:00:13.694
[music intensifies]

662
01:00:22.662 --> 01:00:24.205
- [yelling]
- [Elinda screams]

663
01:00:26.666 --> 01:00:28.292
[Elinda whimpers]

664
01:00:28.376 --> 01:00:30.002
[gasping]

665
01:00:30.878 --> 01:00:31.921
[both grunting]

666
01:00:32.004 --> 01:00:33.256
[gasps]

667
01:00:33.965 --> 01:00:35.007
Run. Elinda!

668
01:00:35.091 --> 01:00:36.509
Run and find Ser Lorent!

669
01:00:37.885 --> 01:00:38.885
[grunts]

670
01:00:39.929 --> 01:00:41.013
[gasps]

671
01:00:41.097 --> 01:00:42.431
[panting]

672
01:00:51.941 --> 01:00:52.941
[yells]

673
01:00:53.901 --> 01:00:55.152
[Rhaenyra panting]

674
01:00:58.072 --> 01:00:59.240
- [gasps]
- [yelling]

675
01:01:01.868 --> 01:01:02.868
[Arryk groans]

676
01:01:14.505 --> 01:01:16.257
- Your Grace!
- Ser Lorent!

677
01:01:16.340 --> 01:01:17.758
[yells]

678
01:01:20.720 --> 01:01:22.638
[Rhaenyra breathing heavily]

679
01:01:23.306 --> 01:01:24.515
[Lorent] With me. Your Grace!

680
01:01:25.016 --> 01:01:26.559
[swords clanging]

681
01:01:30.271 --> 01:01:31.856
Which? Which is Erryk?

682
01:01:33.316 --> 01:01:35.192
- [Erryk yells]
- [groans]

683
01:01:38.321 --> 01:01:39.864
[yells]

684
01:01:42.408 --> 01:01:43.534
We were born together.

685
01:01:44.201 --> 01:01:45.536
You parted us!

686
01:01:46.662 --> 01:01:47.620
[gasps]

687
01:01:47.622 --> 01:01:49.624
But I still love you. brother.

688
01:01:49.707 --> 01:01:51.208
[gasping]

689
01:01:52.043 --> 01:01:53.628
[yelling]

690
01:01:54.253 --> 01:01:55.338
[groans]

691
01:02:05.932 --> 01:02:07.683
[yells]

692
01:02:07.767 --> 01:02:09.143
[gasps]

693
01:02:09.226 --> 01:02:10.478
[yells]

694
01:02:18.152 --> 01:02:20.780
[sobbing]

695
01:02:24.742 --> 01:02:25.785
[body thuds]

696
01:02:34.001 --> 01:02:36.003
[footsteps approaching]

697
01:02:42.677 --> 01:02:43.928
Your Grace.

698
01:02:47.932 --> 01:02:48.933
Erryk.

699
01:02:50.017 --> 01:02:51.435
Forgive me.

700
01:02:52.436 --> 01:02:54.772
- No. No!
- [grunts]

701
01:02:58.067 --> 01:02:59.902
[whimpers]

702
01:03:04.240 --> 01:03:07.702
[Otto] It is ignorance and vanity.

703
01:03:09.745 --> 01:03:13.124
You know as well as I do
that Aegon must be kept in check.

704
01:03:13.207 --> 01:03:15.793
As does Ser Criston.
The two of them together...

705
01:03:17.545 --> 01:03:19.005
Ser Criston is not temperate.

706
01:03:20.423 --> 01:03:23.092
But his devotion cannot be questioned.
If it does come to war...

707
01:03:23.175 --> 01:03:24.343
He's ensured it.

708
01:03:25.511 --> 01:03:29.557
He's young and unschooled.
His faith is in steel and bone.

709
01:03:29.640 --> 01:03:31.392
He has not the long view.

710
01:03:31.934 --> 01:03:32.935
None of them do.

711
01:03:33.936 --> 01:03:35.813
They wish now
not for the good of the realm

712
01:03:35.896 --> 01:03:39.358
but for the petty satisfaction
of vengeance.

713
01:03:39.442 --> 01:03:40.860
[Alicent exhales]

714
01:03:43.237 --> 01:03:44.613
Aegon is still malleable.

715
01:03:45.948 --> 01:03:48.159
It is the death of the child
that has unstrung him.

716
01:03:55.291 --> 01:03:56.876
I can't stay here.

717
01:03:59.253 --> 01:04:01.047
Exiled from the council...

718
01:04:02.882 --> 01:04:06.719
witness to the blundering of our plans.
I'll return to Oldtown.

719
01:04:08.888 --> 01:04:10.514
The Hightowers still have strength.

720
01:04:10.598 --> 01:04:16.020
and you have a son there
who'll take more kindly to instruction.

721
01:04:16.103 --> 01:04:18.773
Daeron may yet help us in weeks to come.

722
01:04:23.944 --> 01:04:25.362
Go rather to Highgarden.

723
01:04:28.365 --> 01:04:31.535
The Tyrells must be taken in hand.
Their bannermen are wavering.

724
01:04:32.661 --> 01:04:34.580
While you're gone.
I'll speak sense to him.

725
01:04:35.289 --> 01:04:38.542
His blood will cool.
In time. you may yet return.

726
01:04:52.765 --> 01:04:54.767
The young are peacocks.

727
01:04:55.684 --> 01:04:57.978
All shrieking and feathers.

728
01:05:00.564 --> 01:05:04.985
But we will yet prevail
and bring forth peace. I still believe it.

729
01:05:06.570 --> 01:05:08.781
As long as you and I hold fast.

730
01:05:21.752 --> 01:05:22.837
I have sinned.

731
01:05:27.550 --> 01:05:29.593
I do not wish to hear of it.

732
01:05:48.988 --> 01:05:50.573
[Aegon sobbing]

733
01:05:57.830 --> 01:05:59.832
[continues sobbing]

734
01:06:03.502 --> 01:06:05.504
[melancholy music playing]

735
01:07:12.446 --> 01:07:13.530
[grunting]

736
01:07:24.667 --> 01:07:26.669
[tense music playing]

737
01:07:31.840 --> 01:07:32.883
[moaning]

738
01:07:44.061 --> 01:07:46.021
[closing theme playing]

738
01:07:47.305 --> 01:08:47.298
